revision.text:
The '''Cherry Kearton Medal and Award''' is an honour bestowed by the [[Royal Geographical Society]] on "a traveller concerned with the study or practice of natural history, with a preference for those with an interest in nature photography, art or cinematography".<ref name="MA">{{cite web|url=http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/825B7F12-0860-4D84-8515-1FFFF5EFE011/0/ListofMedalsandAwards2011.pdf|title=Medals & Awards|publisher=[[Royal Geographical Society]]|accessdate=28 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002055908/http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/825B7F12-0860-4D84-8515-1FFFF5EFE011/0/ListofMedalsandAwards2011.pdf|archivedate=2 October 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>http://www.devgeorg.org.uk/?p=888#&panel1-2</ref> It is named for nature photographer [[Cherry Kearton]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://naturalhistorybookshelf.com/cherry-kearton-biography-of-a-wildlife-photographer/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141015080710/http://naturalhistorybookshelf.com/cherry-kearton-biography-of-a-wildlife-photographer/ |archivedate=2014-10-15 |df= }}</ref> and was launched in 1967.

